◆ ndel_data

int Params::ndel_data
private

Size of bins in Foureir space for power spectrum.

This parameter \( n_{\Delta} \) determines the width of the spherical shells in Fourier space. If the fundamental mode is \( \Delta k \), the width of spherical shells is \( \delta k = n_{\Delta} \Delta k \) such that the arrays defining the spherical shells are defined as \( k_{i} = k_{min} + (i + 0.5)\delta k \) .

Read from input parameter file.

◆ ndel_window

int Params::ndel_window
private

Size of bins in Foureir space for Window function.

This parameter \( n_{\Delta} \) determines the width of the spherical shells in Fourier space used for the window function. If the fundamental mode is \( \Delta k \), the width of spherical shells is \( \delta k = n_{\Delta} \Delta k \) such that the arrays defining the spherical shells are defined as \( k_{i} = k_{min} + (i + 0.5)\delta k \) .

Read from input parameter file.

◆ redshift_space_coords_g

bool Params::redshift_space_coords_g
private

This parameter identif if RSD are included in coordinates.

Set \texttt{false} if the coordinates written in the tracer catalog do not have any effect of peculiar velocities. This can be the case of using Cartesian coordinates in real-space.If power from such input is to be measured in redshift space, go to the pre-proc directive \paramp{\texttt{REDSHIFT\gi SPACE}} (see \Ssec:ppreproc}). If instead, the input catalogs has coordinates with RSD already in the coordinates, set to \texttt{false}.

Read from input parameter file.

◆ sys_of_coord_dm

int Params::sys_of_coord_dm
private

This parameter identifies the system of coordinates in which positions of dark matter particles are written in an ASCII file for a catalog.

0=(Cartesian coordinates (X,Y,Z)). 1=(Equatorial coordinates (RA,Dec,r)). 2=(Pseudo-equatorial coordinates (RA,Dec,z)). 3=(Pseudo-equatorial coordinates (RA,Dec,z)). With sys_of_coord_dm = 2, the code uses a set of cosmological parameters to compute the comoving distance from redshifts. With sys_of_coord_dm = 3, the redshift is directly used as radial coordinate. All distances are given in units of Mpc over h.

Read from input parameter file.

◆ sys_of_coord_g

int Params::sys_of_coord_g
private
Note
coordinate system of the object catalogue

0 → positions are given in Cartesian coordinates (X, Y, Z)

1 → positions are given in equatorial coordinates (RA, Dec, r)

2 → positions are given in pseudo-equatorial coordinates (RA, Dec, z)

3 → positions are given in pseudo-equatorial coordinates (RA, Dec, z)

Note
with option 2, the code uses the set of cosmological parameters to transform redshift z to comoving distance; with option 3, the redshift is directly used as radial coordinate
